    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="535"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 800.6354/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of the Japanese Embassy</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_TT1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tanaka</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Acting Foreign Trade Adviser of the
                        Department of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LJG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 25.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_LJG1">Lay</persName>
                    </hi>: The matter of joining the inter-Allied tin committee, which formed a part
                    of our conversation on the 18th instant, has been duly taken up with my
                    Government who now inform us that a telegraphic instruction was despatched on
                    the 7th of September detailing a member of the Japanese Embassy at London to
                    take part on that committee representing the Japanese Government.</p>
                <p>Yours very truly,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_TT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. Tanaka</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
